This paper deals with the recognition of intersection graphs of geometric objects, which is a topic that falls under computational geometry (cs.CG) and discrete mathematics (cs.DM). The paper also mentions partial orders, which is a topic in both combinatorics (cs.DM) and theoretical computer science (cs.CC). Finally, the paper presents a polynomial-time algorithm, which is a topic in algorithms and data structures (cs.DS) and machine learning (cs.LG). Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.DM and cs.CG, followed by cs.DS, cs.LG, and cs.CC.
